				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Advice about AA<a name="9930"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 8 03 2:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did run 3 at 51, then leveled to 62, and did regen 3, then went back to regular exp for now.
<br />

<br />
I would do run3 asap, then level as much as possible, as AA is MUCH faster as you level up, and the songs you get 61/62/63 are VAST improvements over the ones you had just a few levels prior.  Being able to get into a group, and twist Warong of Zek, Wind of Marr, and either (or both) Warsong of Vah Shir or Psalm of Veeshan is VERY VERY nice.
<br />

<br />
I almost always run a 4-twist, and having 85% haste, a 52 Point DS, Str Maxxed out, resists buffed out real nice, and 36HP and 20 mana per tick regen is sweet.  Compare that to the level 50 and below versions of those songs, and you can see how being even in the lower 60's is a big assest, far better than any AA skills.
<br />

<br />
NO pre-63 bard, with ANY amount of AA will be able to buff EVERY resist at the same time.  Even somewhere mundane like Sebilis greatly benifits from having all resists covered, as the stupid shammy frogs cast magic, cold, poison and disease spells, and the wizzies add fire to the mix, so only having MR/FR/CR or MR/PR/DR doesnt help nearly as much as Veeshan.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
